  "short-title": "NEET",
  "desc": "In the Autonomous Machines thread, you will design, build, and deploy mechanical systems, software, and autonomy algorithms for real-world autonomous machines and robots. Our program of study encompasses several project-based classes that help you develop your individual and group skills for working on the types of complex projects you will encounter in industrial settings. Along with our project-based classes, we will support your pursuit of undergraduate research in autonomy and robotics at MIT through our connections with research faculty and MIT-UROP. In addition to our on-campus activities, you will have opportunities for summer internships in autonomy/robotics with our corporate sponsors."
